# Portfolio & PWA Walkthrough

## Overview
I have successfully designed and built your dynamic, animated, and fully responsive personal portfolio website according to your exact specifications! The website is located in `d:/مشروعي` and is also fully configured as a Progressive Web App (PWA).

## Changes Made
- **Created `index.html`**: Structured all of your provided details including personal info, experience, education, skills, accounting/computer/development courses, languages, Satar and Edraak platforms.
- **Created `style.css`**: Implemented a breathtaking aesthetic utilizing your requested colors (Light Blue, Pink, Purple, Gold).
  - Designed a dark-themed glassmorphism interface.
  - Added animations: floating profile image, typing effect, card lift on hover, and scroll-triggered fade-ins.
  - Built custom Vertical Timelines and Progress Bars.
  - Integrated full RTL (Right-to-Left) support with Arabic Google Fonts (Cairo).
- **Created `script.js`**: Set up the logic for the Typewriter Effect, Intersection Observers (for fade-in animations), Accordions (for Edraak partners), smooth scrolling, and PWA Service Worker registration.
- **Created `manifest.json` & `sw.js`**: Configured the Progressive Web App so it can be installed natively on desktop or mobile devices and work offline.

## How to Test
1. Open the folder `d:/مشروعي`.
2. Add your profile picture and name it `profile.jpg` inside the folder.
3. Add the Satar logo and name it `satar-logo.png` inside the folder.
4. Add two app icons named `icon-192.png` and `icon-512.png` for the PWA if you want custom icons.
5. Open `index.html` in Google Chrome or Edge.
6. **(For PWA Install):** It is highly recommended to run the folder using a local server (like the VSCode Live Server extension or Python's `python -m http.server`) to test the Service Worker and see the "Install App" icon appear in your browser's address bar.

Enjoy your stunning new digital portfolio!
